\begin{proof}
[ Proof of Theorem ~ \ref{thm:reflexive} ]
The polytope $4\calP_G{-}\mathbbm{1}$ consists of the vectors $w \in \IR^m$ satisfying \begin{eqnarray*}
\ph{+} w_a + w_ b + w_c & \ leq & 1 \\ \ph{+} w_a - w_ b - w_c & \ leq & 1 \\ - w_a + w_b - w_c & \ leq & 1 \\ - w_a - w_ b + w_c & \ leq & 1 , \end{eqnarray*} for each degree three vertex $v$ and edges $a$ , ~ $b$ , and $c$ incident to $v$ , for a total of $4n_3$ inequalities , where $n_3$ is the number of degree three vertices in $G$ .
From Liu and Osserman ~ \cite[Prop.~3.5]{LiuO2006} , the polytope $4\calP_G$ is integral , and thus so is $4\calP_G{-}\mathbbm{1}$ .
\end{proof}

