\begin{cor}
Let $G$ and $G'$ be connected $\{1,3\}$ - graphs with the same number of vertices and on the same set $E$ of edges .
Then there exists a bijection $\phi$ between $\calP_G$ and $\calP_{G'}$ such that , for $w'=\phi(w)$ , we have that
$$w'\vert^{}_{X} = w\vert^{}_{X}$$
where $E \setminus X$ is the set of internal edges of arbitrary spanning trees in $G$ and $G'$ .
\end{cor}
